features: [Fireproof & Waterproof] The file organizers are made of double-layered, non-itchy, silicone-coated fiberglass, providing protection for documents against fire with a withstand capability of up to 2000℉. Highly water-resistant, offering a solution for unexpected spills or accidents.

[Neat Storage and Classification] The important document storage feature a unique design that allows for the neat storage and classification of various items, including letter/A4 files, receipts, cards, USB drives, pens, passports, and more. The accordion-style design simplifies file organization, eliminating clutter and saving time and money.

[Convenient Handle for Portability] The fireproof document safe bag are equipped with a convenient handle, ensuring easy portability. This feature allows for effortless transportation and can be a practical solution for users on the go.

[Multiple Function Storage] The accordion file organizers boast 13 individual pockets, 1 zipper pocket, 1 pen pocket, 6 card slots, 4 small mesh bags, 4 medium mesh bags, and 1 main pocket. This provides plenty of room in a compact size of 13.97"x10.43"x1.5", allowing for the secure storage of important documents while effectively classifying and finding files.

[Double Zipper and Colorful Labels] The document bag feature a double zipper for easy opening and closing, ensuring convenient access to files without the risk of losing important documents. Colorful labels are included to simplify the categorization of files, making organization effortless.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 7, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars very professional looking
reviews.reviewText: This has many pockets on the inside, perfect for business cards, or those small steno notebooks. It comes with the labels for the accordion folders. The zippers on it are heavy duty and hefty - they don't feel cheap. This is quite professional looking, especially with its handles, it feels very much like a briefcase without being as bulky as a briefcase. It's very sturdy. I'm not sure if this is fireproof or waterproof, but it certainly feels like it could be. The outside has a rubberized feel which makes it a magnet for cat and dog hair.I'm using it to put the important papers for my work in it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Good for me!
reviews.reviewText: This is perfect for what I wanted it for.To organize 8.5 x 11 targets and maps for the range.It has tons of storage slots for paper.-8.5 x 11 fit very well!-Lots of room for pens and Sharpies!Outside texture feels "rubbery", so it may be water resistant.I don't see how it can be "waterproof" with the zipper.I like it, and it works for me.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 13, 2024
reviews.reviewText: This folder is made really well, it's thick and sturdy and I am confident that my most important documents will be safe in here! It has ample storage and lots of compartments.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Not sure if it's fireproof
reviews.reviewText: It's a nice case. Lightweight. I didn't try putting it in a fire, so I don't know if it's fireproof.The separators are plastic, which might melt? That would compromise papers inside (unless they were in a sleeve.I don't need it to be fireproof. There are 12 pockets, and some nice tags you can right on to make markers to determine what is in a particular sleeve.I look forward to using this for a class I attend to organize my papers.It's a pretty sturdy case, even though it's got some flexibility.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 20, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Secure in many ways
reviews.reviewText: Before this one I was using one without a zipper, which was annoying because when you are in a hurry, like in the airport to show some document, you can easily lose something just by grabbing your organizer.This one has a good zipper that lets everything inside, and an accordion file organizer to identify your documents by type or month of the year, all in a super compact folder that is well finished.Everyone needs an organizer like this for the important documents of your life!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: It's a nice case to bring all your important documents and things to meetings. I don't plan to test out it's fire-proof claim but I've taken it out when snowing heavy and/or raining and I can say it's relatively waterproof in that kind of setting.I'm not a fan of the material itself as it looks and feels weird but it's probably fire-resistant material so it's a minor issue. It doesn't look or feel premium at all but at its price, it's not a premium product. It does the job so I can't really knock it down much. Can't speak on the durability as I've not used it too long yet but will update as I keep using it.Overall, it's not a bad price for the item and I would recommend this to others.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 16, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Effective organization inside
reviews.reviewText: I'm not going to test the fireproof or waterproof claims, but I'm really pleased with this organizer. It is thoughtfully designed, so there's a spot for all common document needs, with room for pens, thumb drives, memory cards, credit cards, passports, ID cards, etc.
